@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "TriCon" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries are
needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must have at least 4
colours.

                             How to play?

  The goal of the game is to create a triangle on the outermost tiles on the
board, for that, you must use all the coloured links that are shown on the
game board. Complete the game in the least amount of moves possible.

  To play, click on any octagonal-shaped tile, if there is at least one
link connected to the tile, it will rotate clockwise by 60 degrees around
that tile. Note that you cannot click on the small dots that surround the
game board, they only serve for the "stray" links to connect to.

  A '@{b}?@{ub}' button appears on the lower left in the game window, clicking on
this button will briefly display the shape to match and then will
redisplay the game board as you left it.

  You can also change the colour of the links by clicking on the coloured
star button located on the lower right of the game board.

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub} button.

  Have fun!

@endnode

